'containsAds': None, 'released': 'May 10, 2012', 'updated': 1591629864, 'version': '2.1.0', 'recentChanges': '  - Global data mode\r\n  - Local data mode\r\n  - Auto raster size\r\n  - Internal improvements', 'recentChangesHTML': '  - Global data mode<br>  - Local data mode<br>  - Auto raster size<br>  - Internal improvements', 'comments': ["The app currently is great. I use it to track lightning in storms when I storm chase. Learning the minute key isn't very hard. Once you use it a bit it becomes easier to understand what type of lighting storm your dealing with when understanding the numbers and size of storm. It's a great app overall and I would recommend that storm chasers use it. Now it only tracks lightning, so there's no other radar settings than the lighting radar.", 'Very good app with surprising number of possibilities.', "Does not include real time tracking like the i is versions low quality graphics , doesn,t really help with storm development , dev. Is rude and unprofessional , we did not kill your app, YOU did, instead of listening to the feedback and try and resolve the issues with Google maps , you down graded the app and then dropped support on Google play because you didn't like the feedback you were getting, then blamed the users for the apps failure rather then take responsibility uninstalling.", "I've used app every thunderstorm! Allows one to easily predict the direction and severity of electrical storms (and when to take cover). In the past, I would witness lightning and wonder about the distance when it wasnt very clear by calculating by time lag of thunder(when thunder constant and omnidirectional). Now i have a clear picture of events in real time. Ive installed another lightning tracker app and toggle between them as they inhance each other. thanks.", 'Works good after the update', "Best app ever until the recent map update. What have you done. The satellite map was clear and excellent. This new map is absolutely awful low resolution and places written in local dialect? It looks like a child drew it. Why ? Please bring back the old map Google satellite may be outdated but its clear and precise. At least give us the choice. Trust me you've shot yourself in the foot with this one", "Bring back satellite maps! I love this app. Well I did until this update! The map no longer has the option for satellite view. The new style looks awful.Every major road is a wishy washy red and look like veins. I never thought I minded the look of veins until now! Or it looks like the stuff in War of the World's that creeps over the ground although that makes it sound cooler than it is. As other users have said, it's now painfully slow to load and the colours on the map are the same as strikes!", "Love this app. Has great data, and it has inspired me to purchase a Blitzortung Lightning Detector to contribute to the data. I wish everyone would get over the openmap situation, if you don't like it go and find an app that provides the 'boring outdated google maps' that costs the developer to provide to you, at cost. I am very happy with this app and will continue to contribute to this amazing science hobby. Thanks guys great work on keeping up with all the bad reviews, and thank you for this app.", 'I have used Blitz happily for years. It appears that the developers have taken it off Play store and turned off data delivery, so my beloved app no longer works. Supposedly it has been migrated to some place called F-droid. But I cant find any way to download a replacement app or even figure out how to use F-droid. So it appears that this wonderful app is effectively no longer available, even for us loyal users. Such a shame.', "The lightning tracking is accurate and sophisticated, but the map is very slow to load (even on fast wifi) and just looks like a blurred pixellated mess. Previous map for older version was significantly better and loaded/zoomed instantly. UPDATE following reply - as constructive feedback, why not have a 'download offline map' option as part of the app? Much better than the first impression of a really fuzzy map.", "Previously rated this app a 1 star due to the map changing from an informative Google earth style to a childish difficult to read OS style. Today I have come to use it and its not displaying any lightning information and an exclamation mark triangle in the top right. This app has been great for ages and now it seems wrecked. I've downloaded blitzortung from the play store from a different author and guess what. It's working and it's a Google earth style map...... Bye bye guys..... Uninstalled!!!", "edit from 4 to 1 star: this app works when it wants. I can't get any infomation and wants location acces. So... i can't see the database without providing location. Data mining or stupid design? I don't care aboute notofication and i don't think this stupid operating system needs location acces to have a map with 150 logos on it.", 'Update from my previous review: Maps are crude and low res and lack contrast...horrible to look at. Rude reply by developer which is a shame. The resolution is so poor you cannot read some of the town names (what few there are) even with the resolution at highest. (as per their suggestion) Only just seen previous reviews by others. Sad. Going to delete app. Pity. RIP', "maps are no longer detailed which is difficult to see where exactly the lightning strikes occur. If there is an error in the app as the developer don't you think you should fix it? It appears however that the entire app has changed. I've since uninstalled. it's not as good as it was.", 'Despite "worse" map in new version I downloaded app from F-Droid store and it works great. After all of this years having no problems with the app it\'s unfair to be so critical for some issues and still having a solution to have the app for free. So thank you guys and keep on the good work!', "Terrible update. This worked fine until you updated to this version. There's no more option 