 to how it was?', "Was a great app until the last update. now it doesn't seem to work properly if at all. keep getting error messages and don't show the storm I was watching", "I can get real time lightening maps online, this thing loads every 60 seconds which seems a bit rubbish when I can just go online and see real time on blitzortung. shame the app isn't as good as the website", 'Its Pretty Good... and would be better if one could get the "strikes Per" on the left side of the display to disappear, as it somewhat obsucates the map...', "🌩️👍🌩️I've tested almost all the Lightning tracker apps and this one is the best, Thanks to a lot of customization and notifications. Hope there will be more. App is free and no ads. 1 thing would be nice : showing stations. Shame it's leaving the playstore due to some entitled and uneducated subhumans 😔.", 'Was a massive part of my UK weather page on Facebook as loved the detail in towns, reliability and accuracy.....however your new update is disappointing and would rather pay monthly before the update.', 'Looking at developer response, I immediately uninstalled.  Clearly they don\'t care what people have to say.  Hard to care about a thing when it\'s creators don\'t.  EDIT:  I guess I need to clarify what I mean.  When a developer responds with: "Do you want to motivate us with the one star? No problem, we removed the app from play store and stopped data delivery. So you can stop complaining about the map."  There is something wrong.', 'this app is a very good implementation of the web site. The ability to add alarms for a radius is very nice as well.', 'As of late the application fails to display any lightning data. There is a triangle with an exclamation point on the top right of the map.', "Satellite map gone :( This isn't navigation app, what is the reason to observe all these roads and streets ... and it's loading so slow now", "The best lightning monitor! I've set it to monitor lightning activity near me in the background 